      info        : "When FIPS mode is enabled on a Docker Engine - Enterprise node, it uses FIPS-validated cryptography to protect the confidentiality of remote access sessions to any bound TCP sockets with TLS enabled and configured. FIPS mode in Docker Engine - Enterprise is automatically enabled when FIPS mode is also enabled on the underlying host operating system.

